      <body>
         <div type="entry">
            <pb facs="https://leaf.bucknell.edu/sites/default/files/2026-01/diary81.jpg"/>
            <dateline><date>Wednesd
<date when="1862-06-25"/>
ay 25</date>.</dateline>
            <p>It was a <name type="weather">fine pleasant day</name>. The morning we spent at bayo<objectName type="equipment"/>net exercise - this
               afternoon Regimental drill. <persName key="Col. Nagel" ref="https://raw.githubusercontent.com/BucknellDSC/jmlinn/refs/heads/main/jmlinn_personography.xml#jmlper167">Col Nagle</persName> was here to make his affidavit for pay -
               he is an essential dutchman though fine looking and said to be a fine drill
               master. He has a queer high toned voice with a squawk to it- he pronounces
               rather oddly - speaking of some thing he said it was his “Karculation”. <persName>Capt Pollock</persName> was here – now a first Lieutenant – the commission <persName key="Lt Col Joshua K Sigfried" ref="https://raw.githubusercontent.com/BucknellDSC/jmlinn/refs/heads/main/jmlinn_personography.xml#jmlper172">Lt Col. Sigfried</persName>
               sent back was returned and the Capt and 1st Lieutenant resigning 3 days after
               he received a commission as 1st Lieutenant. <persName key="Lt Col Joshua K Sigfried" ref="https://raw.githubusercontent.com/BucknellDSC/jmlinn/refs/heads/main/jmlinn_personography.xml#jmlper172">Lt. Col. Sigfried</persName> refused to assign
               him to duty, but <persName key="Col. Nagel" ref="https://raw.githubusercontent.com/BucknellDSC/jmlinn/refs/heads/main/jmlinn_personography.xml#jmlper167">Col. Nagele</persName> took it in hand and assigned him. He talked of
               resigning, but I advised him not do it. There is a feeling because he as a
               corporal was promoted over the heads of sergeants. <persName cert="medium" key="Matthew Vandine" ref="https://raw.githubusercontent.com/BucknellDSC/jmlinn/refs/heads/main/jmlinn_personography.xml#jmlper065" type="real">Vandine</persName> was announced as 1st
               sergeant &amp; <persName key="William Allison" ref="https://raw.githubusercontent.com/BucknellDSC/jmlinn/refs/heads/main/jmlinn_personography.xml#jmlper082">Billy Allison</persName> as sergeant – corporal not filled. </p>
         </div>
